19:T946,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Can a business do the strategy itself and hire someone only for implementation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The AI Roadmap book is a complete self-guided version of the AI Navigator framework — all 11 steps, all templates, all worked examples. A business owner who works through the book systematically produces the same planning documents as a guided engagement, at the cost of their own time rather than a consulting fee."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does the strategy phase cost relative to implementation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For most SME AI implementations, the strategy engagement costs between $997 and $2,497. The implementation cost depends on the specific use cases identified in the strategy — Tier 1 implementations typically cost between $5,000 and $20,000. The strategy engagement typically represents 5 to 15% of the total implementation investment."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is AI strategy a one-time exercise or an ongoing process?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The initial strategy engagement — covering the first 12 months of AI implementation — is a one-time exercise that produces a complete plan. As the business executes that plan and reaches the end of its Phase 1 scope, the strategy is updated."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What if our situation changes between the strategy and the implementation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A good strategy document is not a rigid commitment — it is a living plan. The AI Navigator implementation plan includes explicit risk mitigations and a process for updating the plan when circumstances change. The plan adapts without losing the strategic coherence established in the planning phase."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does a completed AI strategy guarantee a successful implementation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. A strategy is a prerequisite for a successful implementation, not a guarantee of one. Implementation quality — the technical execution of the build — determines whether the systems built match the design. The strategy eliminates the most common causes of AI project failure: undefined goals, ambiguous requirements, wrong tool selection, and inadequate oversight design."}}]}f:[["$","$L2",null,{"id":"faq-schema","type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$19"}}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"article-wrap","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"breadcrumb","aria-label":"Breadcrumb","children":[["$","a",null,{"href":"/","children":"Home"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":"true","children":" › "}],["$","a",null,{"href":"/resources/","children":"Resources"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":"true","children":" › "}],["$","span",null,{"children":"AI Strategy vs AI Implementation — What's the Difference and Why It Matters"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"children":"AI Strategy vs AI Implementation — What's the Difference and Why It Matters"}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"Most businesses in Qatar do not have an AI strategy problem. They have a sequencing problem."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"They move to implementation before strategy is complete. They select tools before use cases are designed. They build before they plan. And then they wonder why the results do not match the investment."}],["$","p","2",{"children":"The distinction between AI strategy and AI implementation is not semantic. It is the difference between building the right thing and building the wrong thing efficiently."}]],"$L1a",["$L1b","$L1c","$L1d","$L1e"],"$L1f","$L20","$undefined","$L21","$L22"]}]]
23:I[9456,["619","static/chunks/619-ba102abea3e3d0e4.js","549","static/chunks/app/(site)/resources/%5Bslug%5D/page-82b918b41d4220bf.js"],"default"]
24:I[6203,["619","static/chunks/619-ba102abea3e3d0e4.js","549","static/chunks/app/(site)/resources/%5Bslug%5D/page-82b918b41d4220bf.js"],"default"]
1a:["$","div",null,{"className":"cta-box","style":{"margin":"32px 0"},"children":["$","$L23",null,{"href":"/","location":"resource_mid_ai-strategy-vs-ai-implementation"}]}]
1b:["$","section","0",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"What AI Strategy Actually Means"}],"$undefined",[["$","p","0",{"children":"AI strategy is the planning work that determines what to build, in what order, for what reason, and how you will know whether it worked. It produces written documents. It requires business judgment. It does not require anyone to write a single line of code."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"A complete AI strategy consists of five core elements: a documented business goal; an honest starting point assessment; a prioritised use case roadmap; AI Task Canvas specifications for each use case; and a phased implementation plan. When all five of these elements exist as written, reviewed, and approved documents, you have an AI strategy."}]]]}]
1c:["$","section","1",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"What AI Implementation Actually Means"}],"$undefined",[["$","p","0",{"children":"AI implementation is the build work that turns the strategy documents into working systems. It consists of: data infrastructure preparation; system development and integration; testing and quality assurance; and deployment and monitoring."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"Implementation done well is efficient, predictable, and produces systems that work as designed. Implementation done without a strategy is a series of discoveries — discovering that the data is not where you thought it was, discovering that the use case was not specific enough to build from."}]]]}]
1d:["$","section","2",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Why Sequence Is Everything"}],"$undefined",[["$","p","0",{"children":"Consider what happens when implementation begins without a complete strategy. A development team is briefed to 'build an AI chatbot for customer service.' They build a chatbot. It answers questions. But which questions? The brief did not specify. In what tone? The brief did not define the brand voice requirements. Six weeks into the build, the business reviews the chatbot and finds it does not match the brand, handles edge cases incorrectly, and has no success metric."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"A McKinsey survey of AI initiatives consistently finds that 50 to 70% of AI projects fail to deliver the intended value — and the most commonly cited cause is insufficient problem definition before implementation begins."}]]]}]
1e:["$","section","3",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"The Compounding Return on Getting the Sequence Right"}],"$undefined",[["$","p","0",{"children":"A business that builds its AI strategy correctly builds AI systems that generate data from the moment they go live. Every customer interaction, every processed document, every delivered recommendation generates data that makes the next phase of AI smarter."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"The difference between these two businesses, 18 months from their respective starting points, is significant. The business with a strategy has AI systems at Tier 3 maturity — demand forecasting, customer segmentation, CLV modelling. The business without a strategy has a collection of tools and a pile of unstructured data."}]]]}]
1f:["$","section",null,{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Frequently Asked Questions"}],["$","$L24",null,{"faqs":[{"q":"Can a business do the strategy itself and hire someone only for implementation?","a":"Yes. The AI Roadmap book is a complete self-guided version of the AI Navigator framework — all 11 steps, all templates, all worked examples. A business owner who works through the book systematically produces the same planning documents as a guided engagement, at the cost of their own time rather than a consulting fee."},{"q":"How much does the strategy phase cost relative to implementation?","a":"For most SME AI implementations, the strategy engagement costs between $997 and $2,497. The implementation cost depends on the specific use cases identified in the strategy — Tier 1 implementations typically cost between $5,000 and $20,000. The strategy engagement typically represents 5 to 15% of the total implementation investment."},{"q":"Is AI strategy a one-time exercise or an ongoing process?","a":"The initial strategy engagement — covering the first 12 months of AI implementation — is a one-time exercise that produces a complete plan. As the business executes that plan and reaches the end of its Phase 1 scope, the strategy is updated."},{"q":"What if our situation changes between the strategy and the implementation?","a":"A good strategy document is not a rigid commitment — it is a living plan. The AI Navigator implementation plan includes explicit risk mitigations and a process for updating the plan when circumstances change. The plan adapts without losing the strategic coherence established in the planning phase."},{"q":"Does a completed AI strategy guarantee a successful implementation?","a":"No. A strategy is a prerequisite for a successful implementation, not a guarantee of one. Implementation quality — the technical execution of the build — determines whether the systems built match the design. The strategy eliminates the most common causes of AI project failure: undefined goals, ambiguous requirements, wrong tool selection, and inadequate oversight design."}]}]]}]
20:["$","div",null,{"className":"cta-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"style":{"marginTop":0},"children":"Ready to assess your AI readiness?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The AI Readiness Assessment evaluates your business across five dimensions — workflow type, decision complexity, data availability, process volume, and team size — and gives you a personalised score with specific recommended next steps. It takes three minutes."}],["$","$L23",null,{"href":"/","location":"resource_bottom_ai-strategy-vs-ai-implementation"}]]}]
21:["$","div",null,{"className":"author-bio","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Allan Sendagi"}]," is the author of ",["$","em",null,{"children":"The AI Roadmap"}]," and founder of SafeHaven AI. He works with SMEs across Qatar and the GCC to build structured AI implementation plans using the AI Navigator framework."]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":8},"children":[["$","a",null,{"href":"/","style":{"color":"var(--brand)","fontWeight":600},"children":"Take the free AI Readiness Assessment"}]," · ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://calendly.com/allan-safehavenai/30min","style":{"color":"var(--brand)","fontWeight":600},"children":"Book a discovery call"}]]}]]}]
